Almost two-thirds of women in Jordan also view abortion as somewhat or very morally acceptable (63%), while a third, however, say it’s not at all morally acceptable. When it comes to favorability toward different groups, however, the majority of people in Jordan hold more negative views toward certain groups as lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender individuals (75% hold at least somewhat unfavorable views). Only 3% say they have a favorable view of LGBT individuals (AGE 16-24 years old). In 2016 Israel approved a new draft law that would annul existing definitions of marriage as only between a man and a woman and instead make marriage available to any two people, regardless of gender, in the country.

Muslim Law to ban marriages over 17 in Bangladesh

After banning marriage for those below the age of 18, Bangladesh will from October 15 also restrict marriage ceremonies for those between 18-21 unless they can prove the birth of a child. Assistant planning minister Meerjady Sabrina Flora said in a statement, “We have amended the previous law. We will check all marriages at the age of [21], so that noone gets married without the birth of a child.”

Pornography not against Islamic principles, says Saudi Arabia

Saudi government has ruled pornography does not go against Islamic principles and law, in a landmark decision supported by women and men alike.
